1. Scope

The scope of work covers the design and fabrication for 6.6kV switchgears.

1.1. General

The purpose of this document is to identify technical specification for 6.6kV switchgears

shall be assuring a safe and reliable supply of electric power to the users.

• The 6.6kV switch gear distribution boards shall generally comprise adequately rated

circuit-breakers for incoming, outgoing and bus sectionalizing circuits as required.

• The distribution boards shall be complete with draw out type circuit-

breakers/contactors.

• The distribution boards shall be so constructed that requisite electrical clearances

are kept between any two live parts and between any live part and earth as

specified in the applicable standards.

• The units shall be constructed to provide for interchangeability of corresponding

parts. However, in draw-out type switchgear distribution boards containing circuit-

breakers/contactors, it shall not be possible to insert circuit-breaker/contactor

trucks with circuit- breakers/contactors of lower current rating into cubicles rated

for high currents.

• The current transformers (CTs) shall be mounted on the side of the breaker/ isolator

away from the main bus bars so as to allow safe and easy access of personnel. CT

secondary leads shall be brought to a short-circuiting type terminal board provided

for testing purpose, before connecting to their respective circuits.

• The cable termination shall be contained within the concerned cubicle forming an

integral part thereof mounted in the rear and shall be freely accessible for cable

[Type here]

