347180ETS802

A

connection. The cable termination chamber shall have adequate space for

termination of the required number, type and size of cables and shall be provided

with suitable bracing so that the weight of the cables does not unduly stress the

terminals. Provision shall be made for earthing of cables of outgoing feeder circuits

over earthing switch duly interlocked with the circuit- breakers/ isolators at both

ends of the cable feeder to ensure that none of the breaker/isolators can be

switched on when the Earthing switch is on and vice versa.

• All low voltage internal wiring of the distribution board shall be of stranded copper

conductor PVC insulated and PVC sheathed wires of core size not less than 2.mm 52

for CT connections, 1.mm 5for 2 other connections. The terminal blocks shall be

conveniently located and not more than two wires shall be connected to one

terminal. Separate blocks shall be provided for distribution of control power. Each

terminal block shall be provided with at least percent 20 spare terminals. All

terminals and links shall be arranged to facilitate easy checking and testing of relays,

instruments etc.

• Control cables within the distribution board shall be carried in flexible conduits or

troughs which shall be accessible for cable replacement and shall be fitted away

from electrical flash-over zones in the board.

• A copper earthing bus of adequate section and of electrically continuous and

mechanically robust construction shall be provided, extended through and solidly

connected to all the units of the distribution board with terminals for connection to

the station earthing system.

• Interlocks shall be provided according to IEC to ensure proper sequence of

operation. (For outgoing earthing, first the circuit breaker shall be in draw out

position. In this position a key switch will be released for earth switch closing)

• Each cubicle of switchboard shall be provided with MCB/MCCB for protection/

isolation of individual auxiliary AC and DC circuits.

