A

• The switch board shall also be provided with main MCB/MCCB for

protection/isolation of incoming AC and DC supply. The presence the AC and DC

shall be controlled by means of flag relay for giving the visual and acoustic alarm in

case of missing.

• All devices, wires and terminal blocks within the board shall be clearly identified by

durable and legible tag corresponding to those used in applicable drawings.

• Each section of the switchboard and devices mounted on it shall be identified by

name plates in the front as well as rear. The name plates shall be made of durable

material with legible lettering. Units shall be numbered consecutively form left to

right when facing the front of the board. Label for all components both on

component and under back board shall be considered.

• MV panels shall be located in separate sub-station room.

• 6.6kV switchgear shall be installed in indoor spaces under the roof. It shall be

modular apparatus made of aligned standards with arc proof units that have been

tested in compliance with IEC 62271-2.

• The panels shall be assembled in one length switchboard. The type shall be metal

clad and air insulated.

• The boards shall be of air insulated, metal-clad and shall be of prefabricated self-

supporting type for indoor installation in industrial plants and shall be designed for

mounting on structural steel base embedded in concrete construction. The boards

shall consist of independent, standardized easily assemble cubicles provided with

front door.

• Moreover, it shall be such as to allow the addition of other cubicles without major

mechanical modification to the existing cubicles.

• The switchgear shall have circuit breakers and earthing switches and also vacuum

contactor for 6.6kV transformers. The circuit breaker shall be of the horizontal draw-

