347180ETS802

A

The design criteria used for the construction of this type of switchboard enables to achieve the

following important features:

• Division of cells as mentioned hereinafter

• Use of automatic shutters on the fixed poles of the circuit breaker, which

• Prevent accidental contacts with the live parts totally

• Visual check from the outside, through a mechanical shock resistant glass

• Window, of the position of the earthing switches

• Grounding of all metallic parts of the switchboard

• Insulation material of high fire-proof degree

1.2.1. Structure

The structural frame of switchboard is made of modular metallic elements bolted together

consisting of steel sheet having thickness not less than mm 2 as well as the front and rear

door, panels. All other enclosures of partitions shall be mechanical strength sufficient to

withstand all the stresses to which they may be subjected during the functioning of the

switchboard.

Each switchboard is always made to be easily extendible on its ends.

All items of small size (screws, squares, hinges crosses, etc.) shall be galvanized.

1.2.2. Grounding

All the metallic structural parts of the switchboard, the no-live metallic parts of the circuit

breakers and the equipment in general, as well as the CTs/VTs secondary, are connected to

the copper ground bar of adequate section which the grounding system on both ends.

The grounding of the doors of the cells is made by means of flexible copper plates.

In general, the continuity of the earthing circuits shall be ensured taking into account the

[Type here]

