The M.V metal clad switchboard characteristics:

Rated system voltage: 6.kV 6

Highest system voltage: kV 12

Number of phases: 3

Rated frequency: 50Hz

Short circuit withstand kA 40 (Second 3)

For CTs installed in MV motor starters with fuse protection, short time current rating is not

applicable.

-Short time current rating is applicable for earthing switches. Earthing switches have adequate

peak withstand current carrying capacity of kA 80 in closed position. However, for the incoming

feeders, the earthing switches also have the rated peak making capacity of kA 100.

• System earthing Isolated or resistance earthed

• Power frequency withstand voltage (60s) 28kV

• Impulse withstand voltage – peak 75kV

• Control voltage Fed by Emergency Power supply

• Protection degree. IPIndoor 42 IPOutdoor 54

1.3. Description of cells

1.3.1. Circuit breaker/contactor cell

It contains the Withdraw-able circuit breaker/contactor and its relevant fixed part.

A vacuum type circuit breaker/contactor is installed on the Withdraw-able truck.

