The Withdraw-able circuit breaker/contactor can reach different 3 positions:

• Service: Main circuit and aux. Circuit connected

• Isolated: Main circuit disconnected – aux. Circuit connected (test position) or aux.

Circuits disconnected (fully isolated)

• Withdrawn: Main circuit and aux. Circuit disconnected.

• Circuit breaker completely withdrawn from the compartment.

In the connected and isolated positions, the circuit breaker/contactor remains inside the

compartment with door closed.

A series of mechanical interlocks are provided to prevent wrong operations.

• Movement of the with draw able module form isolated to service position is isolated

position.

• The earthing switch can be closed only when the with draw able module is in isolated

position

• The circuit breaker/contactor cannot be inserted or drawn-out in closed position

• The circuit breaker/ contactor cannot be closed with the Withdraw-able module being in

between isolated service positions.

• Automatic shutters are closed when the circuit breaker/contactor is moved from the

service position, to totally avoid and accidental contact with the live tarts.

• Movement of the Withdraw-able module from isolated to service position or vice versa

cannot be done with front door open.

• It is possible to lock circuit- breaker/contactor truck in service and isolated positions.

• Bus bar cell

It contains the air insulated copper bus bars, able to withstand the thermal and mechanical

stresses due to short circuit of specified magnitude and duration without any damage and

distortion.

