1.3.2. Cable cell

It contains the current transformers (CTs), the earthing switch and the cable terminal. As

mentioned above, interlocks between the Withdraw-able circuit breaker and the earthing

switch are provided. The cover panel of the cable cell is removable and fixed to the main

structure with bolts. The cable terminations are fully contained within the cable cell.

1.3.3. Auxiliary cell

It contains all the auxiliary equipment. Such as:

• Protection relays

• Instruments

• Controls (lamps, selector switches, breaker control switches etc.)

• Terminal strip

All current transformers (CT) are of cast resin insulated type. The volt-ampere outputs of CT

cores are so selected as to have provision for connection of some additional burden in future.

The accuracy class of all CT cores for protective relaying is 5P. The CT cores for general

protective relaying have accuracy limit factor and 20 those for differential relaying have

accuracy limit factor 20.

The CT cores for measuring and indication will have accuracy class of 0.and 5 saturate at an

over current which is safe for the measuring and indicating instruments (instrument security

factor Fs = 5).

Same CT cores are not used for dual purpose of protection and measuring.

All voltage transformers (VT) are of cast resin insulated type, single phase units which are

connected to form a three-phase system. The VTs will have 25% additional VA capacity over

and above that required for meters, relays and instruments connected initially.

The VTs are protected by suitable HRC fuses on the primary side and MBCs on the secondary

side.

The line VT/bus VT are mounted on an independent draw-out type carriage and arranged so

