Various types of auxiliary relays, flag relays, time delay relays, high speed tripping and inter-

tripping relays, trip coil supervision (monitoring) relay, etc. Are provided as required for the

purpose of indication, control, alarm annunciation, tripping, interlocking, signal transmission,

multiplication of circuit breaker, isolator and earth witch contacts etc. These relays are

provided irrespective of whether they are specifically mentioned in the technical specification

or not.

The tripping and inter – tripping relays are operated by the respective group of protective

relays as required for associated tripping and control duties. Overcurrent relays have two

stages of protection. Low set stage I> has IDMT characteristic and high set stage I>> has DMT

characteristic. Both stages of protection are provided with current and time adjustment

facilities.

Earth fault relays, over voltage relays and under voltage relays have IDMT/DMT characteristics

depending on requirement. Both current/voltage and time are adjustable for these relays.

Motor protection relays are incorporated with thermal overload protection, thermal start-up

supervision, locked rotor/time overcurrent protection, high set overcurrent protection, low set

earth fault protection, phase reversal, phase unbalance and single phasing protection.

All relays for protection and alarming are provided with either flag indicators or LED lamp

indications. All relays are of solid-state type preferably numeric type. All relays are of multi-

contact hand reset.

The ratios, accuracy class and accuracy limit factors of current transformers (CTs), VA burden of

current and voltage transformers indicated in the technical specifications and single line

diagrams are tentative. However, during the detail engineering stage, such adjustment may be

introduced (not affecting the basic design) as may be required in order to suit the final

data/information obtained for the various production and auxiliary facilities, if any, with a view

to install a system satisfactory in every respect for the purpose for which it is intended.

The incoming and bus-section circuit breakers of each switchboard are suitably interlocked to

prevent parallel operation of the two incoming feeders. However, in case of planned shut-down

