1.4. M.V. Circuit breakers

• Nominal voltage: kV 12

• Service voltage: 6.kV 6

• Short time current rating: kA 40 for sec 3

• Operating mechanism: motor operated – spring charged mechanism

The circuit breaker is provided with closing coil, trip coil and antidumping device. The circuit

breaker is also provided with mechanical ON/OFF position indicator and operation counter.

All circuit breakers have natural ventilation.

At least one circuit breaker opening and closing operation is possible after failure of DC supply

to the spring charging motor.

The circuit breaker is provided with a conveniently located manual tripping lever or button for

emergency tripping and testing purposes. A manually operated mechanical device to enable

closing of the circuit breaker without power supply is also provided.

Operating mechanism of circuit breaker is trip free.

Circuit breakers are provided with necessary auxiliary switches for indication, control,

interlocking. Two spare sets of auxiliary contacts, two normally closed and two normally open

shall be left free in each unit wired up to the control cable terminal block. The auxiliary contacts

can be easily converted from normally open to normally closed type and vice versa, if feasible.

The circuit breaker is suitable for making and breaking capacity currents of shunt capacitor

banks controlled by the breakers without any restrict.

Circuit breakers of only proven, well tried out and robust design are used. Only the circuit

